      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SHEZA CARONA (4) after racing outside the leader at the bell made it two wins from her last four runs last start, getting home by 2.75 metres over 1800m at this track  when sent out as the equal favourite in what was her second run this prep. Won't find this any harder and she can go right on with the job. SKINNY HORACE (6) finished second at this track two runs ago before a less impressive effort at his latest appearance over 1800m at this track, beaten 55 metres after racing three-wide over the early stages. Certainly cannot be faulted after that last effort. Good enough to put himself back in the winners' stall. ALBYNITE (3) is worth some thought based on his third over 1609m at Port Pirie two runs ago. CAULONIA PLAYBOY (2) looks the outsider in the small field.",
